<c74object name='av.pix.unpack' category='' module=''>

    <digest>
        Unpack a texture into components (r g b a)
    </digest>

    <description>
        Unpack a jitter texture into its 4 color components (r, g, b, a), send as individual textures to the output (note that these textures are actually 4-plane textures contain in the form of rrrr, gggg, bbbb, aaaa).<br/><br/>

Note: In general it might be more efficient to code per plane processing yourself in a jit.gl.pix with [swiz] and [vec]. But sometimes it might be useful to just combine a texture quickly, or get a single plane from a texture in a larger patch without diving into jit.gl.pix/slab.

    </description>
    
    <discussion>
        
    </discussion>

